Commented on #319 "WebSocket protocol error: httparse error: invalid token" when connect from ngrok tcp tunnel.

I've made a simple tcp server to listen for websocket connections, but the initial message sent to the server seems to be garbled. Here's a request I got on this test TCP server via ngrok: Opened connection from 127.0.0.1:64160 Got string: .*uh&2v51d:0 0xRYx /(}S;?F' ZZ+/,0/5 Dih20.tcp.ngrok.io#-+JJ (7 more lines were trimmed) Could this maybe have something to do with connecting with secure websockets (wss://) over ngrok?
